      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "Hard to knock the consistency of REVERAND BOB (9) who added to a series of top-three results when beaten 3m at Maryborough last week. Scored a win over this distance the last time he raced here. Big chance with even luck from the back row. CLASSIC FAIR (8) hasn't been seen since he led for a fighting win at this circuit and distance in January but was readied with a trial placing. Draws for a trail and is likely to have developed with maturity. MISTER DEVEREAUX (7) was well fancied last week but broke and finished midfield. Had finished in the top-two in each of his other outings this campaign including a Bendigo win two back so is worth another chance. WHISKEY DAWN (3) gets her best draw yet and can be competitive from there. ASPEN BELLE (10) steps up in grade but is making good progress, winning her last two outings.",
